      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1767130921081,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "1. Functional requirements\n        •        Submit jobs with ordered stages\n        •        Stage-level exactly-once start + idempotent submit\n        •        Locks: shared read, exclusive write; multi-lock per stage\n        •        Deadline: 6h to terminal; stage TTL bounds runtime\n        •        Immutable audit + current status\n\n2. Non-functional requirements\n        •        Submit p95 < 150ms in-region\n        •        Safety over liveness for execution during partitions\n        •        Multi-region HA; defined RPO/RTO\n        •        Throughput: 2M/day, 6k/min peak, 3× retry burst\n        •        Cost guardrails: quotas, concurrency caps, admission control\n\n3. API surface\n        •        POST /tenant/{t}/jobs with client job_id + stages + lock intents\n        •        GET /tenant/{t}/jobs/{job_id} materialized status\n        •        GET /tenant/{t}/jobs/{job_id}/events immutable stream\n        •        Internal-only: stage transitions, lock acquire/renew/release\n\n4. Data model & ownership\n        •        Authoritative Job/Stage state in an owner-region store keyed by (tenant, job_id); conditional updates for stage\ntransitions\n        •        Lock store per resource home-region:\n        •        ResourceLock(resource_id, mode, epoch, writer_pending, lease_expiry, version)\n        •        LockHolders(resource_id, holder_id, mode, lease_expiry)\n        •        Fencing token = epoch minted atomically at write-lock acquire\n        •        Audit log append-only:\n            •        by job for normal reads\n            •        by resource_id for lock forensics\n\n5. Components & flows\n        •        Submit: gateway → job API → dual-durable enqueue (local + replicated) → audit event\n        •        Execution: owner-region dispatcher → workers → CAS stage lease → acquire locks → run → commit → release\n        •        Locking: conditional writes enforcing RW compatibility + fairness\n        •        Deadline reaper: marks terminal and triggers lock cleanup\n        •        Audit pipeline: consume events, store hot, roll to cold\n\n6. Tradeoffs & failure modes\n        •        Submit durability vs latency: async forward + replicated log, or dual-write\n        •        Lock fairness policy and starvation prevention\n        •        Token propagation strategy with strict rejection guarantees\n        •        Backpressure: per-tenant budgets + per-resource retry budgets + circuit breakers\n        •        Partition behavior: accept submits everywhere, execution only where gate says READY\n\n7. Constraint changes\n        •        Strict execution pause enforced by a single gate in authoritative registry\n        •        Cross-region submit survival achieved via replicated log or dual-write\n        •        Forensics supported via resource-centric event table/materialization\n        •        Tenant isolation via fair queueing + quotas, with dedicated planes as premium tier",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1. Functional requirements\n        •        Submit jobs with ordered stages\n        •        Stage-level exactly-once start + idempotent submit\n        •        Locks: shared read, exclusive write; multi-lock per stage\n        •        Deadline: 6h to terminal; stage TTL bounds runtime\n        •        Immutable audit + current status\n\n2. Non-functional requirements\n        •        Submit p95 < 150ms in-region\n        •        Safety over liveness for execution during partitions\n        •        Multi-region HA; defined RPO/RTO\n        •        Throughput: 2M/day, 6k/min peak, 3× retry burst\n        •        Cost guardrails: quotas, concurrency caps, admission control\n\n3. API surface\n        •        POST /tenant/{t}/jobs with client job_id + stages + lock intents\n        •        GET /tenant/{t}/jobs/{job_id} materialized status\n        •        GET /tenant/{t}/jobs/{job_id}/events immutable stream\n        •        Internal-only: stage transitions, lock acquire/renew/release\n\n4. Data model & ownership\n        •        Authoritative Job/Stage state in an owner-region store keyed by (tenant, job_id); conditional updates for stage transitions\n        •        Lock store per resource home-region:\n        •        ResourceLock(resource_id, mode, epoch, writer_pending, lease_expiry, version)\n        •        LockHolders(resource_id, holder_id, mode, lease_expiry)\n        •        Fencing token = epoch minted atomically at write-lock acquire\n        •        Audit log append-only:\n            •        by job for normal reads\n            •        by resource_id for lock forensics\n\n5. Components & flows\n        •        Submit: gateway → job API → dual-durable enqueue (local + replicated) → audit event\n        •        Execution: owner-region dispatcher → workers → CAS stage lease → acquire locks → run → commit → release\n        •        Locking: conditional writes enforcing RW compatibility + fairness\n        •        Deadline reaper: marks terminal and triggers lock cleanup\n        •        Audit pipeline: consume events, store hot, roll to cold\n\n6. Tradeoffs & failure modes\n        •        Submit durability vs latency: async forward + replicated log, or dual-write\n        •        Lock fairness policy and starvation prevention\n        •        Token propagation strategy with strict rejection guarantees\n        •        Backpressure: per-tenant budgets + per-resource retry budgets + circuit breakers\n        •        Partition behavior: accept submits everywhere, execution only where gate says READY\n\n7. Constraint changes\n        •        Strict execution pause enforced by a single gate in authoritative registry\n        •        Cross-region submit survival achieved via replicated log or dual-write\n        •        Forensics supported via resource-centric event table/materialization\n        •        Tenant isolation via fair queueing + quotas, with dedicated planes as premium tier",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "KeUPFelvADC6gq-WpNVG5",
      "type": "text",
