      "updated": 1767024186943,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "High-Level Problem Statement\n\nDesign a Job Execution Platform with the following goals:\n\nCore Functional Requirements\n        •        Clients submit jobs consisting of one or more actions\n        •        Each job must execute exactly once globally, even across regions\n        •        Clients may aggressively retry submits with low latency expectations\n        •        Jobs may take seconds to hours to complete\n        •        Jobs may require exclusive access to shared resources (e.g., databases)\n        •        Jobs must survive:\n            •        process crashes\n            •        network partitions\n            •        regional failover\n\nNon-Functional Requirements\n        •        Multi-region active/active\n        •        Horizontal scalability (Kubernetes)\n        •        Strong correctness over availability when necessary\n        •        Cost-aware (avoid runaway compute)\n        •        Auditable execution history\n        •        Clear ownership of “who is allowed to run”\n\nConstraints\n        •        You cannot rely on a single regional leader\n        •        You cannot assume perfectly synchronized clocks\n        •        You cannot assume retries are well-behaved\n        •        You must assume duplicate messages\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "High-Level Problem Statement\n\nDesign a Job Execution Platform with the following goals:\n\nCore Functional Requirements\n        •        Clients submit jobs consisting of one or more actions\n        •        Each job must execute exactly once globally, even across regions\n        •        Clients may aggressively retry submits with low latency expectations\n        •        Jobs may take seconds to hours to complete\n        •        Jobs may require exclusive access to shared resources (e.g., databases)\n        •        Jobs must survive:\n            •        process crashes\n            •        network partitions\n            •        regional failover\n\nNon-Functional Requirements\n        •        Multi-region active/active\n        •        Horizontal scalability (Kubernetes)\n        •        Strong correctness over availability when necessary\n        •        Cost-aware (avoid runaway compute)\n        •        Auditable execution history\n        •        Clear ownership of “who is allowed to run”\n\nConstraints\n        •        You cannot rely on a single regional leader\n        •        You cannot assume perfectly synchronized clocks\n        •        You cannot assume retries are well-behaved\n        •        You must assume duplicate messages\n",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
